<subSubSection pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
The specimen with numerical rounded label (6293) could be the holotype of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Masaridae" genus="Chrysis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chrysis aurichalca" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurichalca">Chrysis aurichalca</taxonomicName>
Lepeletier, which arrived in the Spinola collection with the chrysidids of Latreille. The type is not housed in MNHN (
<bibRefCitation author="Buysson, R du" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" pagination="159 - 169" title="Catalogue des Insectes Hymenopteres de la famille des Chrysidides du Museum de Paris." volume="5" year="1899">du Buysson 1899</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
